Example 1.1
User
What is a convolutional neural network?
AI Response
A CNN uses convolutional layers to automatically learn spatial features from images. Pooling layers reduce
dimensionality. CNNs are the standard for image classification and detection tasks.
Example 1.2
User
What is transfer learning?
AI Response
Transfer learning reuses a model trained on one task as a starting point for another related task, reducing
training time and data requirements significantly.
Example 1.3
User
What is feature engineering?
AI Response
Feature engineering creates or transforms input variables using domain knowledge to improve model
performance. It includes scaling, encoding, and creating interaction terms.
Example 1.4
User
What is a transformer model?
AI Response
A transformer is a deep learning architecture using self-attention mechanisms that process all tokens in
parallel, enabling efficient NLP. GPT and BERT are transformer-based models.
Example 1.5
User
What is an autoencoder?
AI Response
An autoencoder learns a compressed (latent) representation of input data through an encoder, then
reconstructs it with a decoder. Used for dimensionality reduction, denoising, and anomaly detection.
Example 1.6
User
What is precision vs recall?
AI Response
Precision is correct positive predictions / all positive predictions. Recall is correct positive predictions / all
actual positives. F1 score harmonically balances both.
Example 1.7
User
What is the bias-variance tradeoff?
AI ResponseHigh bias = underfitting (oversimplified model); high variance = overfitting (over-complex model). Good
models balance both to minimize total prediction error.
Example 1.8
User
What is an epoch?
AI Response
An epoch is one full pass through the entire training dataset. Multiple epochs are used, and the number is a
key hyperparameter affecting model convergence.
Example 1.9
User
What is overfitting?
AI Response
Overfitting occurs when a model learns training data too well—including noise—causing poor generalization
to new data. Symptoms include high train accuracy but low validation accuracy.
Example 1.10
User
What is deep learning?
AI Response
Deep learning is a subset of machine learning that uses multi-layered neural networks to learn
representations of data. It excels at tasks like image recognition, NLP, and speech synthesis.Section 2: Instruction Following
