Example 1.1
User
What is attention mechanism?
AI Response
Attention allows a model to focus on relevant input parts during output generation. Self-attention in
transformers computes weighted relationships between all token pairs.
Example 1.2
User
What is a decision tree?
AI Response
A decision tree splits data by feature values at internal nodes, with leaves representing predictions. They are
interpretable but prone to overfitting without pruning.
Example 1.3
User
What is transfer learning?
AI Response
Transfer learning reuses a model trained on one task as a starting point for another related task, reducing
training time and data requirements significantly.
Example 1.4
User
What is RLHF?
AI Response
Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback trains a reward model on human preference data, then uses
RL (PPO) to fine-tune an LLM to produce outputs humans prefer.
Example 1.5
User
What is K-means clustering?
AI Response
K-means partitions data into K clusters by iteratively assigning points to the nearest centroid and updating
centroids as the mean of assigned points, minimizing intra-cluster variance.
Example 1.6
User
What is a neural network?
AI Response
A neural network is a series of algorithms modeled after the human brain, consisting of input, hidden, and
output layers, with weights adjusted during training to minimize prediction error.
Example 1.7
User
What is a transformer model?
AI ResponseA transformer is a deep learning architecture using self-attention mechanisms that process all tokens in
parallel, enabling efficient NLP. GPT and BERT are transformer-based models.
Example 1.8
User
What is PCA?
AI Response
Principal Component Analysis reduces dimensionality by transforming data to axes of greatest variance. It
reduces noise, speeds up training, and helps visualize high-dimensional data.
Example 1.9
User
What is word embedding?
AI Response
Word embeddings map words to dense vectors where similar words are nearby. Word2Vec, GloVe, and
FastText are popular methods, used as NLP model input features.
Example 1.10
User
What is backpropagation?
AI Response
Backpropagation computes gradients of the loss with respect to each weight by applying the chain rule
backwards through the network, enabling weight updates via gradient descent.Section 2: Instruction Following
